sentences.text:
2 Orders 2 and 3 made by the Federal Magistrates Court of Australia on 19 May 2006 are set aside and in lieu thereof it is ordered that: 






 (a) order in the nature of an order absolute in the first instance for a writ of certiorari to quash the decision of the second respondent dated 14 January 1998 to affirm the decision of the first respondent not to grant the appellant a protection visa; 









 (b) order in the nature of a writ of mandamus directing the second respondent to hear and determine the application for review according to law; 







 (c) the first respondent pay the applicant's costs.
